I think this is just a problem of nomenclature.  In CSS, a statement such as<p><pre><code>  font-color : red;
</code></pre>
comprises a &quot;property&quot; (left) and a &quot;value&quot; (right).  The draft W3C proposal allows you to specify a &quot;custom property&quot; and assign a value to it, thus:<p><pre><code>  --header-bg-colour : #ff5533;
</code></pre>
You can then reference this elsewhere by saying:<p><pre><code>  header { background-color : var(--header-bg-colour); }
</code></pre>
Isn&#x27;t that just how you use a variable (written as $header-bg-colour) in Sass?
